						<summary>

						<p>Slab lying in front of the ruined temple outside the village.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Tribhuvanamalla [Vikramāditya VI] 12th century A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This highly damaged record states that when Chālukya Tribhuvanamalladēva was ruling over the empire, Aṇnaladēva [a subordinate of the king] made a grant of land probably at Bhattagrama Bēvīnahā[ḷa]. In the date portion only Pushya, amāvāsya is available. It is in characters of the 12th century A.D.</p>						

						</summary>
